## Why This Is Asked
Checks practical API testing of security-critical webhooks, including signature verification, replay protection, and idempotency under concurrency. It also probes tooling choices and test coverage for common failure modes.

## Key Concepts
- HMAC validation with shared secret
- Timestamp replay protection window
- Idempotency via idempotency-key
- Concurrency handling in tests
- Clear pass/fail criteria and tooling

## Code Example
```javascript
// Node.js pseudo-test: verify signature and idempotency key
const crypto = require('crypto');
function isValidSignature(payload, sig, secret){
  const hmac = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret);
  hmac.update(payload, 'utf8');
  return hmac.digest('hex') === sig;
}
```

