## Why This Is Asked
Tests for streaming APIs under real-world conditions are tricky; this question probes end-to-end resilience, ordering guarantees, and schema evolution.

## Key Concepts
- Exactly-once streaming semantics; - Backpressure handling; - Reconnection/backoff; - Failover synthesis; - Versioned payloads via feature flags.

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode for an SSE consumer with dedupe
let seen = new Set();
let lastId = null;
source.onmessage = (e) => {
  const id = e.data.id; if (id) { if (seen.has(id)) return; seen.add(id); lastId = id; }
  // process event
};
```

