## Why This Is Asked

Tests spanning REST and WebSocket protocols evaluate consistency, contract fidelity, and resilience in real-time data pipelines—a critical production challenge in financial applications.

## Key Concepts

- Cross-protocol end-to-end testing
- Consumer-driven contracts (Pact)
- Data drift detection between REST snapshots and WebSocket ticks
- Fault injection and upstream outage resilience
- Backpressure and rate-limit validation under traffic spikes

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo-test snippet for cross-path validation
async function testPriceConsistency(symbol) {
  const snapshot = await httpGet(`/prices/${symbol}`);
  const latestTick = await wsGetLatestTick(symbol);

  // Validate tolerance within one tick interval
  assert(Math.abs(snapshot.timestamp - latestTick.timestamp) <= TICK_INTERVAL);
  assert(Math.abs(snapshot.price - latestTick.price) <= MAX_DEVIATION);
}
```

## Tooling and Success Criteria

**Tooling:** Pact for contracts, k6 for load testing, Chaos Monkey for fault injection, custom assertions for data consistency

**Success Criteria:** <100ms latency variance, <0.1% data inconsistency, graceful degradation during outages, effective backpressure under 10x load spikes

