## Why This Is Asked

Idempotency is a critical pattern in payment systems. Interviewers ask this to assess whether a candidate understands:
- How to prevent duplicate charges (a costly business problem)
- The distinction between idempotent and non-idempotent operations
- Proper handling of edge cases and failure scenarios

## Key Concepts

- **Idempotency Key:** A unique client-generated identifier (UUID recommended) that allows the server to recognize duplicate requests
- **Idempotent Response:** Same response returned for retries, regardless of timing
- **Concurrency:** Multiple simultaneous requests with the same key must be handled safely (typically via database locking)
- **TTL (Time-to-Live):** Idempotency keys typically expire after 24-48 hours

## Code Example

```javascript
// Idempotency test using Jest and Supertest
const request = require('supertest');
const { v4: uuidv4 } = require('uuid');

describe('POST /payments/process idempotency', () => {
  const idempotencyKey = uuidv4();
  const paymentPayload = {
    amount: 5000,
    currency: 'USD',
    card_token: 'test_tok_visa'
  };

  test('TC-01: duplicate request with same key charges once', async () => {
    const firstResponse = await request(app)
      .post('/payments/process')
      .set('X-Idempotency-Key', idempotencyKey)
      .send(paymentPayload);

    const secondResponse = await request(app)
      .post('/payments/process')
      .set('X-Idempotency-Key', idempotencyKey)
      .send(paymentPayload);

    expect(firstResponse.status).toBe(200);
    expect(secondResponse.status).toBe(200);
    expect(firstResponse.body.transactionId).toBe(secondResponse.body.transactionId);

    // Verify single charge via external API or database
    const chargeCount = await getChargeCount(idempotencyKey);
    expect(chargeCount).toBe(1);
  });

  test('TC-04: high concurrency with same key', async () => {
    const concurrentRequests = Array(10).fill(null).map(() =>
      request(app)
        .post('/payments/process')
        .set('X-Idempotency-Key', idempotencyKey)
        .send(paymentPayload)
    );

    const responses = await Promise.all(concurrentRequests);
    const transactionIds = responses.map(r => r.body.transactionId);
    const uniqueIds = [...new Set(transactionIds)];

    expect(uniqueIds).toHaveLength(1);
  });
});
```

